<br>
I, being a bit of a silly druid who loves water and waterfalls, decided to look at the beautiful waterfall I could see waaaaay down in a huge crevasse in Paineel. (Yes, those of you that are experienced with this particular area already know what I'm going to say.) My thought was to gently float to the lake that I could see a short ways down and admire the waterfall from there. Much to my surprise, as I nearly reached a nice sturdy stone ledge, I suddenly zoned. 'A zone right in the middle of thin air?' I thought to myself, wondering what would happen next. When I finally did reappear, levitate was gone and I fell quite a long ways. Needless to say, I died. I was told by an 'ever so helpful' FV guide that I am completely out of luck and he would not assist me. Apparently this is considered a 'legal' death. I am sure you all know what I was thinking at this point. He suggested that I form a rescue party. I do not wish to risk the lives of others to bail me out of the stupid situation in which I find myself so what I am asking for instead is some directions on how to enter 'The Hole' the proper way so that I may at least try to find my corpse myself. The clock is ticking and my corpse is rotting so any advice anyone could offer would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Many thanks good people!<br>
<br>
Donjira Windsong    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wessley>Wessley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 4:36:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=884.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trouble in 'The Hole'. Have some advice?</span><hr size=1> The proper way into The Hole is to walk down past the warrens entrance to the pond.  You'll notice a rock.  You can buy the key in Paineel for (I think) 200pp or so, or a rogue can pick the lock.<br>
<br>
The other way to get in is to swim into the rock, duck, then unduck.  Do that a few times and you'll pass through the rock.  It's a bit frowned upon.<br>
<br>
Once you get in, you should probably know that you're going to be KoS and lots of things in The Hole see invis.  Seeing as you're a druid, you're most likely neutral and your best bet is to get a necro to summon your corpse.  Failing that I believe some brell worshippers are not KoS.  You might be able to get one of them to help you out.<br>
<br>
Failing all of that, and assuming your corpse hasn't rotted...if you send me a tell in game I'll do my best to help out.<br>
<br>
